returns.declareDuty.title = Do you need to declare vaping products for duty?
returns.declareDuty.heading = Do you need to declare vaping products for duty?
returns.declareDuty.checkYourAnswersLabel = declareDuty
returns.declareDuty.caption.text = Declare vaping duty
returns.declareDuty.change.hidden = DeclareDuty

returns.enterDutyAmount.title = Amount of vaping products released
returns.enterDutyAmount.heading = Amount of vaping products released
returns.enterDutyAmount.checkYourAnswersLabel = EnterDutyAmount
returns.enterDutyAmount.p = You must declare the total volume in millilitres of finished vaping products you released for consumption this period.
returns.enterDutyAmount.p1 = When calculating duty, round the volume to the nearest:
returns.enterDutyAmount.list1 = 0.1 millilitre for products containing less than 1 litre
returns.enterDutyAmount.list2 = 1 millilitre for products containing 1 litre or more
returns.enterDutyAmount.p2 = For products containing less than 1 litre, enter the volume to one decimal place.
returns.enterDutyAmount.p3 = For example, 999.94 millilitres rounds to 999.9 millilitres.
returns.enterDutyAmount.caption.text = Declare vaping duty
returns.enterDutyAmount.q = How much vaping products released do you need to declare?
returns.enterDutyAmount.details.key = What ‘finished product’ and ‘released for consumption’ mean
returns.enterDutyAmount.details.value.p1 = Finished product means the product is contained in its final packaging for retail sale, or it has had a duty stamp applied.
returns.enterDutyAmount.details.value.p2 = Product released for consumption means that the goods have left a tax-free warehouse to be sold or used in the UK.
returns.enterDutyAmount.q.hintText = Total millilitres of vaping liquid
returns.enterDutyAmount.q.ml = ml

returns.enterDutyAmount.error.nonNumeric = You must enter a number greater than zero
returns.enterDutyAmount.error.required = You must enter a number greater than zero
returns.enterDutyAmount.error.invalidDecimalPlaces.wholeOnly = Enter whole millilitres for amounts of 1,000 ml or more
returns.enterDutyAmount.error.invalidDecimalPlaces.maxOne = Enter no more than 1 decimal place for amounts less than 1,000 ml. For example 999.9
returns.enterDutyAmount.error.exceedsMaxDuty = The volume you entered would result in a duty amount that exceeds the maximum allowed. Enter a volume of {0} or less
returns.enterDutyAmount.error.mustBeGreaterThanZero = You must enter a number greater than zero
returns.enterDutyAmount.change.hidden = EnterDutyAmount

